# Feature Development Workflow

Implement features **in this order**. Complete each step before starting the next.

## 1. Schema type definitions

Add types in `packages/shared/src/types/`. Export from `packages/shared/src/index.ts`. Rebuild: `pnpm --filter @financial-healthcheck/shared build`.

## 2. API service business logic, routes, and tests

| Concern | Location |
|---------|----------|
| Business logic | `apps/api/src/services/<feature>.service.ts` |
| Routes | `apps/api/src/routes/<feature>.ts` — mount in `app.ts` |
| Tests | `*.test.ts` alongside (Vitest + supertest) |

## 3. Frontend components and unit testing

- Components: `apps/web/src/components/`
- API helpers: `apps/web/src/lib/api.ts`
- Unit tests: `apps/web/src/**/*.test.tsx` using `renderWithProviders` from `src/test/test-utils.tsx`
- Run: `pnpm --filter @financial-healthcheck/web test:unit`

## 4. Frontend routes

- Pages: `apps/web/src/pages/` — wire in `App.tsx`
- Use React Query for server state; shadcn + TanStack Table for UI

## 5. Testing

| Layer | Location | Runner |
|-------|----------|--------|
| API | `apps/api/src/**/*.test.ts` | Vitest + supertest |
| Client unit | `apps/web/src/**/*.test.tsx` | Vitest + React Testing Library |
| Client E2E | `apps/web/tests/e2e/` | Playwright |

```bash
pnpm test          # unit tests
pnpm test:e2e      # Playwright E2E
```

Before finishing: shared types built, API tests pass, component unit tests pass, E2E covers the primary user flow.
